China reiterated its commitment to "one country, two systems" for Taiwan, unveiling an anti-secession law that Taiwan strongly opposes.
President Chen condemned Beijing's unilateral move to change the Taiwan Strait's status quo, calling it a threat to regional stability.
The proposed law aims to legalize a potential military invasion of Taiwan, sparking concerns about freedom of speech and cross-strait exchanges.
Both the US and EU criticized China's plan, urging peaceful dialogue.
Taiwan plans to counteract the law and pass a resolution against it, emphasizing the need to defend its sovereignty amidst escalating tensions.
